                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "1) Core Components Selection: Due to the low voltage, low power limitations of PMFCs (1), the sensor node requires an energy conversion stage which boosts the PMFC's output voltage and buffers its energy into a supercapacitor for a duty-cycled operation of the sensor node. We selected the BQ25505 IC by Texas Instruments for this purpose. Besides featuring ultralow quiescent current (325 nA) and an efficient ship mode draining only 5 nA, this IC provides a "
                                },
